    <p>
            There isn't a separate document outlining the Annual Learning Plan.
            There are several examples online but the only Ministry references
            are in Appendix H of the TPA manual. Also, it only includes a
            secondary example. Theoretically every teacher must complete one
            every year, however, that is not always the case. ALPs must be
            completed in a TPA year.
